article.description: Dominique Allen's two first-quarter rushing touchdowns paved the way for a rout of Wofford 39-12 on Saturday afternoon.
article.headline: The Citadel uses ground attack to dump Wofford 39-12
article.linkText: The Citadel uses ground attack to dump Wofford 39-12
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Dominique Allen's two first-quarter rushing touchdowns paved the way for a rout of Wofford 39-12 on Saturday afternoon. Allen has seven rushing touchdowns so far this season. It's the second time in his career he's had multiple rushing scores in the same quarter. Allen ran for 72 yards on the day and was 7 for 10 passing for 125 yards and a touchdown. The Bulldogs (3-2 overall, 2-0 Southern Conference) took a 36-12 lead when Allen completed a 24-yard touchdown to Brandon Eakins with 2:30 remaining in the third quarter. The Citadel's Tyler Renew had 15 carries for 85 yards rushing and a touchdown, while Reggie Williams added a rushing touchdown. Wofford's Ray Smith ran for 58 yards and a touchdown. Evan Jacks was 5 for 7 with 89 yards passing and R.J. Taylor had 86 yards receiving on five catches. The Terriers (3-3, 1-1) were outgained 398-245.
